name: California Association of Food Banks
description: Supports a network of food banks to alleviate hunger and improve food security in California.

name: California Community Foundation
description: Connects donors with causes and provides grants to address critical issues in the state.

name: California State Parks Foundation
description: Protects and enhances California's state parks for future generations to enjoy.

name: California Wildlife Center
description: Rescues and rehabilitates injured and orphaned wildlife in California.

name: California Community Colleges Foundation
description: Supports California's community colleges and student success initiatives.

name: California Native Plant Society
description: Promotes the appreciation and conservation of California's native plants.

name: Feeding California
description: Unites the state's food banks to end hunger and improve nutrition for all Californians.

name: California Bicycle Coalition
description: Advocates for safe and accessible bicycling throughout California.

name: California Art Club
description: Promotes traditional fine arts and representational art in California.

name: California Film Institute
description: Celebrates film as art and education through screenings, festivals, and programs.

name: California Wilderness Coalition
description: Protects California's wild lands and rivers through conservation and advocacy.

name: California Preservation Foundation
description: Advocates for the preservation of California's historic places and cultural heritage.

name: California Foundation for Stronger Communities
description: Invests in nonprofit organizations addressing pressing issues in California.

name: California Native American Heritage Commission
description: Preserves and protects Native American cultural resources and heritage in the state.

name: California ReLeaf
description: Promotes the planting and care of trees for healthier urban environments in California.

name: California Urban Forests Council
description: Advocates for urban forestry and tree planting in communities across the state.

name: California Missions Foundation
description: Preserves and restores California's historic missions and associated monuments.

name: California Youth Connection
description: Empowers foster youth to improve the foster care system in California.

name: California School-Age Consortium
description: Supports out-of-school time programs and services for California's youth.
